        - NODE_BRANCH=7 added to encoding (to be folded into ω via A3)
        - TODO(A1): GPU kernel parity via unified pic.reduce pass

[ ] 2b. `while` loop lowering is unsound — always evaluates both branches 🔴
        # Lowering.c:759-788 — the while loop is lowered by:
        #   1. Evaluating the condition via lowerExpression()
        #   2. Evaluating the body via lowerExpression()
        #   3. Emitting an ω(-, branch) node to select between them
        # Problem: both condition AND body are evaluated eagerly before the branch fires.
        # The body is lowered unconditionally. This means any side effects in the loop
        # body (I/O, mutation) execute regardless of the condition, and any recursive
        # call in the body (which is how loops are implemented) always recurses.
        # A correct lowering must emit the body as a λ-thunk (γ⁺ node) that only fires
        # when the branch selects it, mirroring how `either` works.
        - Wrap loop body in a γ⁺ thunk: lowerExpression the body into a separate MLIR
          func, then emit a γ⁺ agent pointing to it; the branch node's true-wire holds
          this thunk rather than the already-evaluated body result
        - Similarly wrap the false (exit) path
        - Add test/test_while_soundness.lin: loop with side effect verifies effect fires
          exactly N times, not N+1

[x] 3. Beta-reduction (function application at runtime)
        - Phase 1: γ(+,f) ~ γ(-,f) wires aux ports (p1↔p1, p2↔p2)
        - Collapsed checkBeta into standard annihilation per A3
        - GPU kernel parity via unified pic.reduce pass (A1)
        - Phase 2: body-graph cloning for multi-arg / closures

[x] 4. mlir-op full pipeline connection
