## 🟡 Tier 2 — Language Completeness

[ ] 10b. Linearity of principal ports is not statically enforced 🟡
        # Invariant 1 from the spec. There is no pass that verifies every principal port
        # connects to exactly one wire. The current implementation relies on programmer
        # discipline in Lowering.c. Known violation: proj_N dangling p2 (see item 4d).
        # Known risk: env_free() links unconsumed vars to ε, but if a var is used more
        # than the δ-chain accounts for, the extra reference leaves a double-connected port.
        - Add a pic.graph verification pass: walk all AgentOps and assert each principal
          port (p0) appears in exactly one LinkOp or WireOp in the same block
        - Run this pass in debug builds after lowerExpression() completes
        - Emit a structured diagnostic (file:line:col, var name) on violation
        - Integrate into `linc check` subcommand

